The 73rd NHK Asadora Drama is Kaze no Harukacoma% written by Omori Mika. The story is on Mizuno Haruka from Yufuincoma% Oita Prefecturecoma% which is known as a hot spring resort. At the age of ninecoma% Haruka moves from Osaka to Yufuin with her father Yosuke and her younger sister Asuka because Yosuke hopes to open a restaurant in the town. Her mother Yukocoma% howevercoma% chooses to stay in Osaka and the parents soon get a divorce. Yosuke starts running a restaurant but ends up closing it down soon after. Ten years latercoma% Haruka supports her family by working part time while going to a junior college. Worrying about Harukacoma% Yuko invites her to come to Osaka and offers her a job. Although she has not forgiven her mothercoma% Haruka decides to earn money in Osaka to help Yosuke reopen the restaurant. Through various experiences in Osakacoma% Haruka gradually understands her mother and grows as a tour planner with her talent for pleasing people. The drama depicts Haruka's struggle to regain family ties and to realize her dream

The format for Big Brother in Canada remains largely unchanged from the U.S. editioncoma% making them the only two version of the series thus far to follow this format. HouseGuests are sequestered in the Big Brother House without contact with the outside world. Each weekcoma% the HouseGuests take part in several compulsory challenges that determine who will win foodcoma% luxuriescoma% and opportunities to become the Head of Household (HoH) or win the Power of Veto (PoV). The winner of the weekly HoH competition is immune from nominations and nominates two fellow HouseGuests for eviction. The two HouseGuests nominated for eviction are also referred to as being "on the block" for eviction. After a HouseGuest becomes HoHcoma% he or she is ineligible to take part in the next HoH competition. The winner of the PoV competition wins the right to save one of the nominated HouseGuests from eviction and take them off the block. If the PoV winner exercises the powercoma% the HoH then nominates another HouseGuest to go up on the block for eviction. HouseGuests also take part in the Have vs. Have-Not competitions. Depending on their performance during the competitionscoma% HouseGuests are divided into either the "Haves" or the "Have Nots." The Have Nots are restricted to eating "Big Brother Slop" and a couple of food items selected by the viewing public. They are also allowed to eat condiments and protein shakes. Have Nots are only allowed to take cold showerscoma% and typically sleep on uncomfortable beds in a room with poor aesthetics. On Eviction Nightcoma% all HouseGuestscoma% except for the HoH and the two nominees on the blockcoma% vote to evict one of the two nominees. This compulsory vote takes place in the Diary Roomcoma% where voting HouseGuests are asked by the show's hostcoma% Arisa Coxcoma% whom they want to evict. In the event of a tiecoma% the HoH casts the deciding votecoma% announcing it in front of the other HouseGuests

On Eviction Nightcoma% all HouseGuestscoma% except for the HoH and the two nominees on the blockcoma% vote to evict one of the two nominees. column1: MYSTERIES OF THE ABANDONED - SEASON 02 EPISODE 8 - SEA FORTRESS OF DOOM
column4: Scattered around the world are long-forgotten engineering marvelscoma% decaying cities and empty factories that once stood on the cutting edge of design and construction. Today they are discardedcoma% dangerouscoma% and some of them are even deadly. "Mysteries of the Abandoned" reveals why these engineering triumphs were built and how they were left to crumble. In each hour long episodecoma% stories tell of who originally designed the structurecoma% its historical significancecoma% and why it was ultimately no longer viable. California's Goat Canyon Trestle railwaycoma% Pennsylvania's Kinzua Viaduct steel bridgecoma% the Grand Goulets Road in the French Alpscoma% and Hashima Islandcoma% a once thriving and now deserted Japanese islandcoma% are among episode subjects.
